---
import ContentPageLayout from '../../layouts/ContentPageLayout.astro';
import { Scale, UserCheck, Lock, ShieldCheck, Handshake, GraduationCap, Users, Bot, Mail } from 'lucide-astro';

const lang = 'en';
---

<ContentPageLayout
  title="Code of Conduct - eFlury Consulting"
  description="The eFlury Consulting code of conduct: honesty before sales, human-in-the-loop, confidentiality, responsible AI use — the same rules we actually deliver by."
  lang={lang}
  heroTitle="Code of Conduct"
  heroSubtitle="How we work, decide and handle AI — set down bindingly"
  lastUpdated="July 23, 2026"
  keywords="code of conduct, business ethics, responsible AI, human-in-the-loop, confidentiality, eFlury Consulting"
>
  <p>This code applies to eFlury Consulting and to every specialist working on our projects. It is not a declaration for the gallery: it records the same rules we actually deliver by — published in our <a href="/en/method/">method</a> and on the <a href="/en/trust/">trust page</a>.</p>

  <h2>Core Principles</h2>
  <div class="coc-grid">
    <div class="coc-card">
      <Scale size={20} />
      <h3>Honesty before sales</h3>
      <p>Proof, not promises: figures are labelled as estimates, fictional examples are declared fictional. If an automation is not worth it, we say so — even if it costs us the engagement.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="coc-card">
      <UserCheck size={20} />
      <h3>Humans stay responsible</h3>
      <p>AI prepares, people decide. Critical steps carry explicit approvals (human-in-the-loop) — a principle built into every solution we deliver.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="coc-card">
      <Lock size={20} />
      <h3>Confidentiality</h3>
      <p>Client data, processes and trade secrets stay protected — contractually (NDA on request) and technically. We do not talk about client projects without consent.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="coc-card">
      <ShieldCheck size={20} />
      <h3>Data protection</h3>
      <p>We process personal data in accordance with the Swiss Data Protection Act (revFADP). Details are set out in the <a href="/en/privacy/">privacy policy</a>.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="coc-card">
      <Handshake size={20} />
      <h3>Fixed scopes, fair prices</h3>
      <p>Fixed prices, named deliverables, decision gates after every phase. No open-ended effort sinks, no hidden costs.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="coc-card">
      <GraduationCap size={20} />
      <h3>Quality &amp; continuous learning</h3>
      <p>Documentation is part of the work, not an afterthought. We keep our knowledge of models, tools and regulation current — and pass it on.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2><Bot size={20} class="h-icon" /> Responsible AI Use</h2>
  <div class="info-box">
    <ul>
      <li>Client data is not used to train AI models; where possible, we pseudonymize before every API call.</li>
      <li>AI outputs are reviewed, never adopted blindly — where mistakes are costly, we produce drafts instead of automatic dispatch.</li>
      <li>AI-generated examples and demos are declared as such.</li>
      <li>We name the limits openly: language models can be wrong. We build processes so that errors surface before they cause damage.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2><Users size={20} class="h-icon" /> How We Treat Each Other</h2>
  <p>We work respectfully, directly and without condescension — with clients, specialists and everyone who deals with us, regardless of origin, gender, age, religion, disability or sexual orientation. Harassment, demeaning comments and sharing private information without consent have no place in our work.</p>

  <h2>Conflicts of Interest</h2>
  <p>We recommend tools and vendors based on their fit for the client, not on margin. Where our own interests exist — such as partnerships — we disclose them before making a recommendation.</p>

  <h2>Intellectual Property</h2>
  <p>We respect intellectual property rights and expect the same from our partners. Work products are handed over according to the contractually agreed ownership and usage terms.</p>

  <h2>Specialists in the Project Pool</h2>
  <p>Anyone joining projects via our <a href="/en/careers/">career portal</a> commits to this code — the same standards for everyone working under the eFlury Consulting name.</p>

  <h2><Mail size={20} class="h-icon" /> Reporting &amp; Enforcement</h2>
  <p>Violations of this code can be reported to <a href="mailto:me@eflury.com">me@eflury.com</a>. Every report is reviewed personally and receives a response; consequences depend on severity and circumstances. Anyone reporting in good faith has nothing to fear.</p>

  <h2>Governing Law</h2>
  <p>Our conduct is governed by Swiss law, in particular the Data Protection Act (FADP) and the Code of Obligations (CO).</p>
</ContentPageLayout>

<style>
  .coc-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0 2rem;
  }

  .coc-card {
    background: var(--card-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    border-radius: 14px;
    padding: 1.35rem 1.5rem;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
  }

  .coc-card :global(svg) {
    color: var(--teal-text);
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
  }

  .coc-card h3 {
    font-size: 1.02rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin: 0 0 0.4rem;
  }

  .coc-card p {
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .coc-card p a {
    color: var(--teal-text);
  }

  :global(.h-icon) {
    color: var(--teal-text);
    vertical-align: -3px;
    margin-right: 0.35rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 700px) {
    .coc-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
